        <!-- GAME DESCRIPTION -->
        <div class="game-info">
          <h2>Keno Stop Shot</h2>
          <p>
            Keno Stop Shot is another keno variant with an added twist. The
            player selects 1–10 numbers from a range of 1 to 40. The draw then
            begins, revealing numbers one by one. The draw continues until a
            “stop shot” appears — there are three of them in the pool. All
            numbers drawn before the stop shot count toward the player’s
            matches, and the payout is based on how many selected numbers were
            hit before the draw ends. The tension comes from not knowing how
            long the draw will last. RTP is 96.12%
          </p>
        </div>

